<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23680] entrypoint.sh does not accept arbitrary UIDs, returning as an error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23680</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Openshift supports running pods using arbitrary UIDs (&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/3.7/creating_images/guidelines.html#openshift-specific-guidelines)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/3.7/creating_images/guidelines.html#openshift-specific-guidelines)&lt;/a&gt;&#160; to improve security. Although entrypoint.sh was developed to cover this feature, the script is returning an error&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is that the script uses getent to find the passwd entry of the current UID, and if the entry is not found it creates an entry in /etc/passwd. According to the getent man page:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
EXIT STATUS
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; One of the following exit values can be returned by getent:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 0&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Command completed successfully.
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Missing arguments, or database unknown.
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; One or more supplied key could not be found in the database.
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 3&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Enumeration not supported on &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; database.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And since the script begin with a &quot;set &lt;del&gt;ex&quot; command, which means it turns on debug and breaks the script if the command pipelines returns an exit code other than 0.&lt;/del&gt;-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Having that said, this line below must be changed to remove the &quot;-e&quot; flag from set command:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/v2.3.0/resource-managers/kubernetes/docker/src/main/dockerfiles/spark/entrypoint.sh#L20&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/v2.3.0/resource-managers/kubernetes/docker/src/main/dockerfiles/spark/entrypoint.sh#L20&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/v2.3.0/resource-managers/kubernetes/docker/src/main/dockerfiles/spark/entrypoint.sh#L25-L34&lt;/p&gt;</description>
